---
description: Supabase/Postgres access and query habits
globs: lib/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Clients

- Use `lib/supabase/server`, `client`, or `admin` helpers as already established — do not create parallel Supabase singletons without reason.

# Queries

- Prefer explicit `.select` columns when responses are large.
- Handle `{ error }` from Supabase; map to user-safe messages at the API boundary.
- Use pagination (`.range`) for lists; avoid unbounded `select *` on big tables.

# Security

- Respect RLS: use the server user client for user-scoped reads/writes; use admin client only where the codebase already does for trusted server operations.
- Never trust raw client input — validate before inserts/updates.

# Types

- Keep shared domain types near `lib/types.ts` or feature modules; avoid `any` on rows.
